        "content": "<p>Why does <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=LowerAdjoint#doc\">docs#LowerAdjoint</a> exist in its current form? I'm not saying it shouldn't - it's just I can imagine a world where we have <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=GaloisConnection#doc\">docs#GaloisConnection</a> as a bundled structure, and obviously we have it unbundled, but <code>LowerAdjoint</code> is a semibundled version and this feels to me like a weird design pattern.</p>",
